title: Why El Salvador elected a self-proclaimed 'coolest dictator'
description: On Sunday, President Nayib Bukele won reelection in El Salvador in a landslide. Today, The Post’s Mary Beth Sheridan addresses what’s behind Bukele’s striking popularity, his self-proclaimed nickname on social media and his controversial war on gangs.

title: U.S. strike kills militia leader in Baghdad, officials say
description: The action comes after a large wave of airstrikes last week in retaliation for the recent death of three U.S. soldiers.

title: John Bruton, who spurred peace talks as Irish prime minister, dies at 76
description: Mr. Bruton helped keep negotiations on track leading to a landmark 1998 agreement that largely ended decades of sectarian violence in Northern Ireland.

title: Expect to see a lot more of Prince William after father’s cancer diagnosis
description: William may end up taking on more public engagements while other senior members of the British royal family have stepped back.

title: Putin interview with Tucker Carlson shows Kremlin outreach to Trump’s GOP
description: The ousted Fox News anchor went to Moscow to interview Vladimir Putin but was contradicted by the Kremlin when he insisted Western media refuse to talk to the Russian president.

title: Trapped between two wars, Ukrainians in Gaza plead for an exit
description: Members of a once-vibrant Ukrainian community in Gaza say they feel forgotten as evacuations stall and Russia’s war complicates Kyiv’s ability to get their families to safety.

title: Polar bear’s iceberg snooze melts hearts, wins wildlife photo award
description: The finalists in the Wildlife Photographer of the Year award, which was chosen by 75,000 people, include two lionesses doting on a cub and a turtle communing with a dragonfly.

title: Pliosaur, T. rex of the sea, is the Jurassic monster of the moment
description: An amazing fossil find and David Attenborough have helped boost the profile of this marine predator that lived in the age of dinosaurs.

title: Hamas offers multistage hostage return, cease-fire as Blinken visits Israel
description: The Hamas response is to the proposal hashed out by negotiators in Paris and parts of its are likely to be rejected outright by Israel.

title: These vending machines are giving out free STI tests. Can they save lives?
description: A U.K. study seeking to overcome barriers to testing for sexually transmitted diseases found that more than half of users were taking their first STI test ever.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Blinken in Israel to discuss proposal to free hostages and pause fighting
description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken said there was “a lot of work to be done,” while Qatar’s prime minister said Hamas’s response to the proposal was generally positive.

title: Ousted three times before, Pakistan’s Nawaz Sharif may get another shot
description: While his main opponent, Imran Khan, remains in prison, Sharif’s political fortunes have changed.

title: Pakistan stages another unfair election
description: Pakistan’s national elections on Thursday echo the nation’s controversial 2018 vote.

title: House GOP fails to pass Israel package as congressional impasse continues
description: The vote left uncertain the path ahead for funding several security priorities. A Senate bill has been called “dead on arrival” if it reaches the House.

title: Hamas gives ‘positive’ reply to proposal for hostage release deal
description: A draft framework agreement would see a six-week pause in fighting and the release of all civilian hostages held by Hamas in exchange for Palestinian prisoners held in Israeli jails.
